        <p class="show-more-less-text__text--more" tabindex="-1">
          Built a Java-based console matchmaking system as a team project, focusing on backend logic, secure user onboarding, and database-driven workflows.<br>The system supports account creation with 20+ validated attributes, including optional profile fields, OTP-based email verification, and session-based login handling. Each user attribute is validated individually to ensure data integrity and consistency.<br>Implemented profile editing, preference-based match discovery (age range, city, combined filters), and like / mutual-like logic, where contact details are revealed only after mutual interest.<br>Additional features include profile export to text files with conditional data visibility, account deletion, and seamless navigation across all flows without dead ends.<br>My primary contribution involved backend implementation using JDBC, custom data structures for learning purposes, exception handling, file I/O, and functional programming concepts such as lambda expressions and predicates.<br>Email credentials removed from the repository for security reasons
            

    
    

