            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          Built an end-to-end Deep Learning project for real-time Facial Emotion Recognition using FER-2013 🙂📷
This was a great hands-on learning experience covering:
✅ Data loading and preprocessing pipeline (48x48 grayscale to 224x224 RGB)
✅ Transfer learning experiments across multiple architectures (VGG16, ResNet50, MobileNetV2, EfficientNetB0)
✅ Class imbalance handling with computed class weights
✅ Data augmentation for better generalization
✅ Model training with callbacks (EarlyStopping, ReduceLROnPlateau, ModelCheckpoint, CSVLogger)
✅ Evaluation using confusion matrix, classification report, and per-class accuracy
✅ Live webcam inference using OpenCV + trained Keras model
Final selected model:&nbsp;EfficientNetB0-based (Model 8)
Validation Accuracy:&nbsp;66.03%
Validation Loss:&nbsp;0.995
Tech stack:&nbsp;Python, TensorFlow/Keras, OpenCV, NumPy, Matplotlib, Scikit-learn
Built as part of my deep learning journey with&nbsp;AlmaBetter and Woolf&nbsp;and a strong focus on practical computer vision workflows.
Still improving minority-class emotion performance and overall robustness. Always learning and building! 🚀
📂 GitHub: https://lnkd.in/gbQ3hjPW
#MachineLearning #DeepLearning #ComputerVision #EmotionRecognition #TensorFlow #Python #OpenCV #DataScience #ProjectBasedLearning #AlmaBetter #Woolf 
        
