            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          I'm happy to upload this post in LinkedIn 😄 

#120dayschallenges
#Pythonfullstack
#python 🐍 

🎬 Project Highlight: IMDb TV Show Reviews Analysis
 📍 An in-depth data analytics project aimed at understanding viewer sentiment and uncovering trends in TV show ratings on IMDb.

✍ PROJECT DESCRIPTION:-
▪️ I have recently completed a project based on  IMDb TV Show Reviews Analysis on data analysis, where I worked with real-world health data to derive meaningful insights. Using the Pandas library in Python, I read the dataset using read_csv() and performed data cleaning operations such as removing null or unnecessary values with the drop() function.
 " data=pd.read_csv("project.csv")
 data " 
▪️ I also used the value_counts() method to analyze the frequency of different categories and patterns within the dataset, which helped in understanding the data distribution more effectively.

 " data["age"].value_counts().plot(kind="hist")"
🔧 Tools &amp; Technologies Used:
Python – For data handling and scripting.
Pandas &amp; NumPy – For data cleaning, manipulation, and statistical analysis.
Matplotlib &amp; Seaborn – For creating detailed visualizations.
Jupyter Notebook – For combining code, visuals, and explanation in one place.
📊 Key Functionalities &amp; Steps:
Data Collection:
 Gathered a dataset containing IMDb reviews and ratings of various TV shows across genres like drama, comedy, thriller, etc. The dataset included fields like show name, genre, average rating, number of reviews, review texts, and user ratings.
Data Cleaning &amp; Preparation:
Removed missing and duplicate entries.
Handled inconsistencies in review formats.
Processed numerical and textual data to make it suitable for analysis.
Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA):
Analyzed rating distributions across different genres.
Identified the highest-rated and most-reviewed shows.
Compared user ratings over time to find trends or shifts in audience interest.
Visualization:
Created bar charts, histograms, and line plots to show viewer engagement, average ratings by genre, and time-based trends.
Highlighted which genres received consistently high or low reviews.
Insights Extracted:
Found correlations between genre and audience ratings.
Observed that certain genres (like drama and thriller) had higher user engagement.
Identified underdog shows with excellent ratings but fewer reviews.
🎯 Objective:
 The goal was to leverage data analytics to provide actionable insights about TV show performance on IMDb. This analysis could help:
Viewers discover quality shows they might have missed.
Content creators understand what genres and themes are well-received.
Streaming platforms in recommending shows based on audience trends.
📈 Project Outcome:
 This project demonstrates the power of data analytics in entertainment. With the help of Python and visualization tools, I was able to transform raw data into visual stories that reveal real patterns in viewer behavior.

