          🔹 Day 23 of 50 | 50 Days of LeetCode Challenge
Problem: Minimum Time to Make Rope Colorful 🎯
This problem reinforced the importance of greedy algorithms — making locally optimal choices to achieve a globally efficient result. The task was to minimize the total time required to remove consecutive balloons of the same color while ensuring no two adjacent balloons are identical.
By carefully selecting which balloon to remove (keeping the one with the higher removal cost), the solution efficiently achieves the goal in O(n) time and O(1) space.
💡 Key Takeaways:
Greedy decision-making can simplify complex problems.
Optimization often comes from focusing on what to keep, not just what to remove.
Consistency and clarity in logic lead to elegant solutions.
Each day of problem-solving strengthens not just algorithmic thinking, but also decision-making under constraints — a core skill in both coding and life.
#Day23 #LeetCode #CodingChallenge #ProblemSolving #GreedyAlgorithm #DSA #ContinuousLearning #SoftwareEngineering
Shishir chaurasiya PrepInsta
        
            </p>

