            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          Day 94 of 160 :
 📌 Topic: Serialization &amp; Deserialization of Binary Trees
 📚 Concept: Preorder Traversal with Null Markers
Today, I tackled a classic and crucial problem in tree-based data structures — storing and reconstructing a Binary Tree.
🧠 What I learned:
✅ Serialization: Converting a binary tree into a linear ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt; using preorder traversal, while marking null nodes with -1.
 ✅ Deserialization: Rebuilding the exact original tree by recursively reading this list using a class-level index tracker.
💡 Why this matters:
Serialization is foundational when transmitting or storing complex structures like trees (e.g., in databases, files, or networks). This also forms the basis of solving interview problems in platforms like Leetcode, GFG, and others.
🔧 Key Highlights:
1. Used recursive preorder traversal.
2. Maintained tree structure via sentinel (-1) for null nodes.
3. Practiced clean code structure with helper methods.
4. Ensured correctness via full reconstruction and in-order verification.
#gfg160 #geekstreak2025
        
            </p>

