          🚀 Day 24/60 — Consistency compounds

Another day of solving the Problem of the Day (POTD) on GeeksforGeeks as part of my #geekstreak60 challenge.

🧩 Problem: Sum of Subarray Minimums

At first glance, checking the minimum for every subarray feels like a brute-force nightmare.

But the key insight is:
👉 Use a Monotonic Stack to determine how many subarrays each element can be the minimum for.
This pattern transforms the problem from O(n²) thinking to a much more efficient solution.

Problems like this highlight how powerful data structure patterns can be in optimizing algorithms.

🔥 Current streak: 24 days

Thanks to GeeksforGeeks and National Payments Corporation Of India (NPCI) for encouraging developers to stay consistent through #geekstreak60.

Every day of practice is one step closer to stronger problem-solving skills.

💬 Quick question for developers:
Which DSA pattern took you the longest to understand?
1️⃣ Monotonic Stack
 2️⃣ Sliding Window
 3️⃣ Dynamic Programming
 4️⃣ Two Pointers
Curious to hear your experience 👇

