          🚀 Day 97/100 – #DSA Challenge
 Consistency &gt; motivation — one problem at a time 💪
✅ Solved Today:
 LeetCode 1019 – Next Greater Node in Linked List (Medium)
Problem: Given a linked list, for each node, find the next node with a strictly larger value. If none, return 0.
Approach:
 Used a stack to keep track of indices and fill the next greater node values efficiently in one pass. Classic monotonic stack technique for linked list problems.
Takeaway: Understanding stacks for “next greater/smaller” patterns is crucial in competitive programming and coding interviews!
#DSA #LinkedList #LeetCode #ProblemSolving #CodingChallenge #Stack #Java
        
            </p>

