            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          🚀 DSA Fundamentals – Part 3: Prefix Sum (Arrays)
Continuing my DSA fundamentals learning journey 📚
Today, I learned the Prefix Sum pattern — a powerful technique to optimize subarray and range sum problems.
🔹 What is Prefix Sum?
 Prefix Sum is a technique where we precompute cumulative sums of an array to avoid recalculating sums again and again.
🔹 When to use it?
 ✔️ Subarray sum problems
 ✔️ Range sum queries
 ✔️ Cumulative calculations
 ✔️ Repeated sum operations
🔹 Why it matters?
 It helps reduce time complexity from O(n²) to O(n) in many sum-related problems.
⚠️ Common mistakes to avoid:
 • Off-by-one errors
 • Incorrect range subtraction
 • Forgetting to handle index 0
 • Wrong prefix array initialization
📊 I’ve added a visual image explaining:
 • How prefix sums are built
 • How to calculate subarray sums
 • Time &amp; space complexity
 • How to identify Prefix Sum problems
💡 DSA is about mastering patterns, not solving random questions.
📌 Today’s pattern: Prefix Sum (Arrays)
#DSA #DataStructures #Algorithms #PrefixSum #Arrays #Coding #PlacementPreparation #Java #Python #LearningJourney
        
            </p>

