                line-clamp-2">
              
          Day 23/60 – Problem of the Day (POTD) Challenge ✅ 
Today’s problem on GeeksforGeeks was “Sum of Subarray Minimums.”
A great exercise in applying Monotonic Stack patterns to optimize subarray computations.
🔍 Key Insight:
Instead of checking every subarray (which would be O(n²)), I calculated how many subarrays each element contributes to as the minimum element using Previous Less Element (PLE) and Next Less Element (NLE). This brings the solution down to O(n) time complexity.
✅ Results:
• Test Cases Passed: 1120 / 1120
• Accuracy: 100%
• Time Taken: 0.18s
• 🔥 Current Streak: 23 days
Each problem like this strengthens understanding of stack-based algorithms and array patterns, which are very common in coding interviews.
Consistency is the goal - learning something new every day. 💡
#Day23 #60DaysOfCode #GeeksforGeeks #ProblemOfTheDay #DataStructures #Algorithms #Python #CodingJourney
        
            </p>

